<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-06-1025 </DOCNO><TEXT>The authors evaluate the effect of gravity on the probability of vacuumdecay through bubble nucleation for a scalar field in an arbitrary curvedbackground up to first order in an expansion in powers of Rsub(rho) /sup-2/. R is the scalar curvature of the background metric at the locationof the bubble and rho-bar is the size of the bubble as it would appearin a flat space.</TEXT></DOC>